oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Bloomb=
erg News reports</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The US Su=
preme Court agreed to use a case over Nvidia Corp.=E2=80=99s crypto-mining =
revenue to consider making it harder for shareholders to press securities f=
raud lawsuits.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Nvidia is seeking to stop an=
 investor suit that accuses the company of being deceptive about how depend=
ent it was on revenue from crypto mining before a 2018 market downturn. The=
 justices said Monday they will hear Nvidia=E2=80=99s contentions that the =
complaint lacks enough specificity to go forward. ...</p><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">In the newest case, the shareholders say that in 2017 and 2018 N=
vidia=E2=80=99s Chief Executive Jensen Huang hid the fact that record reven=
ue growth was being driven by mining-related sales of the company=E2=80=99s=
 flagship GeForce GPU product, rather than by sales for gaming.</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The investors say the cryptocurrency market=E2=80=99s =
volatility meant the company was exposed to more risk than it was revealing=
. The company said in November 2018 that had missed its revenue projections=
, sending shares tumbling more than 28% over two days.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">Huang at the time said a =E2=80=9Ccrypto hangover=E2=80=9D was =
to blame.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CAnalysts immediately rec=
ognized this as a reversal of NVIDIA=E2=80=99s prior reassurances that mini=
ng-related demand represented a small portion of revenues,=E2=80=9D the sha=
reholders told the Supreme Court.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">Ah yes! Nvidia lulled its shareholders into believing that it was mostl=
y a gaming company, so they bought its stock because they were optimistic a=
bout gaming, but really it was mostly a crypto company, and when the crypto=
 market suffered setbacks in 2018 those shareholders lost money.<a class=3D=
"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
